      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get both have points, but u kinda phrased it like we have to \"prioritize\" law and security while just \"acknowledging\" the human rights stuff? it feels like u put the sovereignty side as the main priority and the humanitarian side as just an afterthought. if u had to pick one as the more \"fundamental\" moral truth, which one would it be?",
